expandedfoods.latest_changelog:
Updated to 1.7.4!

- Wildcraft stuff:
-- Nuts working in fruit bread
-- Nuts working in muffins
-- Nuts working in trail mix
-- Nuts can be put into yogurt meals
-- Sumac and Juniper berries are NUTS now, I guess
-- Wildcraft Aged liquids disabled when Expanded Foods is installed
-- Aged flower wine incorporated into EF
-- Pickled veggie barrel recipes aligned (now requires 1.5 L of vinegar instead of 0.1 L)
-- Updated to use new names for huckleberries, honeysuckle, and pandan
-- Soulstorm slop accepts all poisonous Wildcraft berries

BALANCING:
- Cooked veggies can be added to salad & cold pasta
- Hot pasta can be made with broths
- Cooked pasta can be added to stews
- Candied fruit can be added to yogurt meals
- Nuts can be added to fruit bars
- Peanuts can be added to fruit bread/muffins
- Broth in stew require 0.5 L instead of 1 L; should stop conflicting with soup recipe
- Animal feed breadcrumbs now have 0 grain sat instead of no sat; will now be affected by container perish speed multipliers

BUG FIXES:
- Apple visuals in muffin/fruit dough fixed
- Au gratin not displaying cheese visuals fixed
- Fruit bar apple overlay visuals fixed
- Chopped mushroom transforms fixed
- Onion & bellpepper goes into oven and fruit press properly
- Soups actually accept amaranth and spelt grain
- Primitive Survival snake nuggets visuals fixed
- Broth text renders properly in stews
- Soft acorn dough visuals fixed
- Some chopped mushroom properly poison you now

MISC:
- Liquid lard & resin now harden and dump out into solids (thanks to pizza2004)
- Mixing items grouped together so handbook recipe entries aren't flooded
- Fruit bread/muffin overlay textures no longer have any transparency

terraprety.latest_changelog:
By popular demand, the Terra Prety 7.0.5 update fixes some unintentional consequences of a last minute tweak to 7.0.4 which effectively threw the terrain balance off and inflated medium sized foothills far too much, which essentially erased a lot of plains regions and made mountains less noticeable and impressive. This update also significantly increased inland lake generation. Worlds on previous updates will still play fine. We now intend to turn our sights toward preparing for 1.21, and then starting on what will likely be a long process of trying to develop proper river generation. Wish us luck! ðŸ¤ž

If you have had previous versions of 7.0 installed, you will need to remove the "TerraPrety.json" file located in your ModConfig folder before playing so that the mod can generate an updated file. As usual, this update is NOT compatible with previous versions, you must start a new world to play this update.

With 7.0.5 corrected everything should now be balanced and working properly, and should much better reflect the intended worldgen design (this time I swear!). Will now very likely be the last release for 7.0 until 1.21 (cross my heart, hope to die) unless we've overlooked something big, but that seems unlikely now. Previous versions of 7.0 will still play fine.

rustboundmagic.latest_changelog:
Rewrote the debuff system! This was kind of in before with rust sickness but needed a lot of work to support actual debuffs. This was done to allow my to apply negative effects to many aspects of the mod besides the classic, hurt/hunger drain/stability drain/explosion I currently have. With this rewrite, numerous debuffs have been added.
 
Note that not all debuffs are being used right now. I would like to have a debuff tied to each element. Currently debuffs are appied through spellforge failures.
 
    - Blind = Darkens the screen, not able to see.
    - Disarm = Drops the main hand item.
    - Drift = Spring into the air randomly, potentially taking fall damage.
    - Flickerfire = Moving causes minor damage.
    - Frozen = Drastically lowers body temperature.
    - Lucent Agony = Lose satiety first, then health over time while in the light (14 or higher light level).
    - Manaburn = Lowers current mana by 0-2 per second.
    - Paralysis = Unable to move.
    - Recoil = Casting or using magic of any kind causes minor self damage and knockback.
    - Rust Sickness = Applies a rust void visual distortion.
    - Silence = Unable to cast spells.
    - Umbral Agony = Lose satiety first, then health over time while in the dark (12 or lower light level).
    - Weakness = Increases damage from elemental attacks by 2x.
    - Weighted = Unable to jump, slows movement speed by 50%.
    - Wither = Reduces max HP by -50%. If health is below max when this expires, that lower number will be the current health. 
 
WIP/Future debuffs. No idea how to do these atm, but someday...
- Confusion = Movement keys are reversed. Need to figure out how to swap key inputs.
- Overgrowth = Spawns grasses or leaves near the player slowing movements and block paths. Not sure if I want this one in.
- Soulrot = No idea, needs to have teeth to it. 
- Stasis = Strips off all active buffs and prevents other buffs from being applied.
 
Fire = Flickerfire
Water = Disarm
Wind = Drift
Earth = Weighted
Lightning = Paralysis
Frost = Frozen
Nature = Overgrowth
Arcane = Confusion
 
- The effects list bar will no longer show up if no buffs or debuffs are active. Didn't know that a simple bar would trigger so many since I had the static "effects list" old bar always displayed too! This also means you can only move the bar around when you have effects.
-  Added more robust, on demand checks to the cast bar logic. This should fixed an issue that made the spell scrolls cast bar stay out when consuming a scroll completely.
- Stairs variant block should work in multiblock structures again.
- Added config settings for spell scrolls.
     - Scroll cast time has changed. The default is now 0. If it is 0, it uses the original cast time of the of the spell the scroll has. Any other values will be static cast times in seconds.
     - Scrolls now have cast time modifiers for each tier of spell. This is multiplied to the above cast time. Default is 1.0f (no change). This allows users to further effect specific spells based on spell tier.
     - Scrolls grimoire durability costs (amount of durability used to create a spell scroll) is now broken down into separate tiers.
     - Scrolls now have max durability modifiers, broken down into each tier. Defaults are tier 1 = 4 uses, tier 2 = 2 uses, tier 3 = 1 use.
- Fixed all utility block recipes.
- The oculus portal visuals have changed. Now when a cipher is thrown in, the colors and particles are rust themed instead of, well debug green...
- Fixed an issue where gateway essence costs displayed on the block info of the gateway pedestal did not include calculations with the config modifier.
- Non-mages can now see basic information while looking at the gateway core and pedestal blocks.
- Non-mages can now interact with gateway pedestals. They will only be able to choose a new destination. There is no access to the keystone itemslot.
- The crucible now recognizes enchanted stone items when held.
- The gateway essence cost would sometimes come up with no essence cost if the destination gateway was very close. There is now a minimum of 1 essence.
- Fixed a potential issue where the spellforge research could sometimes fail to produce an item.
- Fixed an issue that would sometimes trigger attunement exhaustion debuff when equipping an attunement core.
- Changed the rest of the recipes that take glimmering and seer's compound to take the equivalent amount of rustic compound.
- Fixed an issue where the utility block achievement would not trigger when crafting the item, only when picking it up.
- Added additional null checks to meshdata tesselation for the oculus.
- Added new configs to the Spellforge that lets people set the success rates per cipher tier. Had to rework the spellforge spell discovery system.
- The spellforge failures now can trigger various debuffs now! Be careful! <3
- Added additional logic to make sure buffs and debuffs are cleared on death.
- Removed an old config option having to do with tier 4 magic.
- Forced a refresh of the general config to make sure things are working right with the packet changes.
- Fixed an issues in the guidebook where I had some duplicate texts.
- Fixed an issue where blind shaders were overwritten by rust sickness. Blind was given priority over rust sickness.
- Fixed an issue with the essence generator where rust sickness would be overwritten to 5s, even if the current duration was 5+ seconds.
- Fixed the issue where random spell selection would sometimes go outside of the array bounds for the spellforge.
- Mod was built against 1.20.12.
